<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-47-0368 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper considers in a general way approaches to the determination ofeconomic merit for hydropower projects in comparison with alternativebut equally viable solutions. Special attention is paid to the impactof proposals for undergrounding water circuits and power house on theevaluation process and on the design decisions that have to be taken.Both conventional hydro and pumped storage schemes are dealt with. Theinfluence of environmental factors is reviewed and the special problemsof the developing countries are examined. Brief conclusions on the appraisalof undergrounding are drawn.</TEXT></DOC>